-- Credit Suisse's Nilesh Jasani Said to Quit to Join Jefferies in Hong Kong
-- George Smith Alexander
-- 2010-07-28T14:09:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/credit-suisse-s-nilesh-jasani-said-to-quit-to-join-jefferies-in-hong-kong.html

          
          
             Nilesh Jasani  quit Credit Suisse
Group AG today to join  Jefferies Group Inc. , according to two
people with knowledge of the matter.  
 Jasani, who was appointed as  head of research  for Credit
Suisse’s Indian operations in July 2006, will be based in Hong
Kong as head of research for the Asia-Pacific region at the New
York-based brokerage, one of the people said, declining to be
identified before a public announcement.  
 Jasani had been head of equity strategy for Asia, excluding
Japan, for almost three years at HSBC Securities (Asia) Ltd.
before joining Credit Suisse in 2005, according to a July 2006
statement from the Swiss company. He had previously worked at
CLSA Emerging Markets and SG Securities, it said.  
 Jasani, 40, didn’t immediately respond to e-mails seeking
comment.  Sheel Kohli , a spokesman for Credit Suisse in Hong Kong,
and  Tom Tarrant , a Jefferies spokesman in the U.S., declined to
comment.  
